\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Halos are biased tracers of the dark matter density field.
 We denote this bias as 
\begin_inset Formula $\bh,$
\end_inset

 which is in general a function of spatial separation.
 We define halo bias as 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\bh(r)\equiv\xihm(r)/\ximm(r).
\]

\end_inset

On sufficiently large scales halo bias is approximately linear, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\bh(r)$
\end_inset

 approaches a constant value 
\begin_inset Formula $\bhlin.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order to measure the bias of a sample of simulated halos, for both Bolshoi
